European Coal Derivatives Retreat 0.6%, Second Consecutive Drop

-- B y   A l i s t a i r   H o l l o w a y
-- 
2011-03-30T12:26:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/european-coal-derivatives-retreat-0-6-second-consecutive-drop.html
Benchmark European coal derivatives
fell for a second consecutive day.  Coal for delivery to Amsterdam, Rotterdam or Antwerp with
settlement next year fell 75 cents, or 0.6 percent, to $128.75 a
metric ton by 1:07 p.m. in  London .  The data are drawn from information supplied by ICAP Plc,
 GFI Group Inc. (GFIG) , Spectron Group Ltd., Credit Suisse Group AG, IHS
McCloskey, Bloomberg, Tradition Financial Services and Tullett
Prebon Plc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alistair Holloway in London at 
 aholloway1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter@bloomberg.net . 